commit.message: Take PR408 and make sure we do the same thing with a similiar call.

Per Issue 418 tweak a few preprocessor macros to get it compiling
against mingw64.

Per Issue 430 review O*Schema::setFromPrevious and O*Schema::getNumSamples to
make sure the former increments the latter appropriately.

Add several unit tests for them.

Because O*Schema::setFromPrevious does not update the number of samples
correctly. (#431)  We instead work around getNumSamples being incorrect by
keeping track of the total number of samples set thus far.
Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/master' into abcstitcher_hold

Introduce a -hold option which instead of writing empty samples for missing
frames instead sets the previous frames data.
